gemini_prompt.main:
Based on the following Anglican theological alignment scores (out of a total of 48), identify one significant historical Anglican figure (like a theologian, bishop, or key layperson) who embodies a similar balance of views.

Scores:
- Catholic: {{catholic}}
- Protestant: {{protestant}}
- Liberal: {{liberal}}

Provide the name of the figure and a brief, one-paragraph explanation (no more than 4 sentences) of why they are a good match, focusing on their historical context and theological contributions. Respond in {{language}}.
